                " \n \nPART-TIME LECTURER POSITION\nFACULTY OF SCIENCE: DEPARTMENT OF ENVIRONMENTAL, WATER AND EARTH SCIENCES\nREF: 24/83\nThe Faculty of Science: Department of Environmental, Water and Earth Sciences requires the services of a Part-Time Lecturer for day classes at the Pretoria (Arcadia) Campus. \n \nKey performance areas \n\u2022 Preparing and conduct lecturers for Full-Time students. \n\u2022 Lecturing the following modules, which are offered in Diploma, Advanced Diploma and Postgraduate: \n- Geophysics I- Introduction to Geophysical methods \n- Geophysics IV- Data processing and interpretation of geophysical maps \n- Geophysics V-Application of Geophysical method and report writing. \n\u2022 Advanced presentation Skills \n\u2022 Geophysical data collection, processing, and interpretation of Geophysical maps. \n\u2022 Proven ability in using teaching technology. \n\u2022 Setting and marking all assessments. \n\u2022 Participating in departmental meetings and subject meetings. \n\u2022 General administration such as capturing test and assignment marks and uploading documents on Brightspace. \n\u2022 Student consultation. \n \nMinimum Requirements: \n\u2022 Master\u2019s Degree in Geology or Geophysics. \n\u2022 Three years teaching and/or industrial experience in Geophysics or other related fields. \n\u2022 Registration with the South African Council for Natural Scientific Professions (SACNASP) will be an advantage. \n \nSend your CV with application for employment form, certified copies of qualifications & ID to: gerberme@tut.ac.za@tut.ac.za\n \nEnquiries: Prof L Monyatsi \nTel: 012 382 6201 \n \nClosing Date: 25 June 2024\n \nWomen and People with disabilities are encouraged to apply.\n \n \n ",
                " \n \n \n \nPART-TIME LECTURER POSITIONS X 7\nFACULTY OF SCIENCE: DEPARTMENT OF CHEMISTRY\nRef: 24/81\nThe Faculty of Science: Department of Chemistry requires the services of seven (7) part-time Lecturers for day classes for the second semester of the 2024 academic year at the Pretoria (Arcadia) Campus. \n \nCritical Performance Areas \n\u2022 Preparing and conducting lecturers, practicals and tutorials. \n\u2022 Compile or update learner guides and prepare study materials. \n\u2022 Preparing and Marking of assessments. \n\u2022 Monitoring and tracking of students performance. Students consultation. \n\n\u2022 Use MyTutor (Brightspace) virtual learning environment to enhance the teaching and learning experience. \n\u2022 Participate in departmental meetings, subject group meetings and committees. \n\u2022 Liaise with departments/ Faculties receiving service from the Department of Chemistry and assist in interventions to improve the success rate of Students. \n\u2022 Conduct ad-Hoc duties as assigned by the line manager. \n \nMinimum Requirements \n\u2022 Relevant Master\u2019s Degree in Chemistry. \n \nExperience:\n\u2022 Three (3) years relevant teaching experience in Chemistry and/or 3 years experience in industry. \n \nKnowledge and Skills: \n\u2022 Full proficiency in English and good communication skills. \n\u2022 Excellent presentation and communication skills. \n\u2022 Proficiency in Office packages (Microsoft Word/Excel/PowerPoint; SharePoint, Teams) and other relevant computer programmes in the TUT environment. \n\u2022 Completion of a TUT license to Teach programme will be compulsory. \n \nSend your CV, certified ID copy, Academic Record and proof of registration for 2024 to the following:Email: MthombeniMS@tut.ac.za\n \nEnqueries: Dr VJ Tembu Tel: 012 382 6288/ 012 382 6284\n \nNB: All applications should be made electronically. Enquiries and an expression of interest, CV and a full academic record should be sent via email. Students who are not registered for year 2024 will not be considered. \n \nClosing Date: 25 June 2024 \n \nIf we have not responded within a period of a month from closing date, you should regard your application as unsuccessful. Correspondence will be entered into only with short-listed candidates. The University reserves the right not to make an appointment. It is the intention of the University to promote representativity in respect of race, gender and disability through the filling of these posts. Preference will be given to candidates from the designated groups.\n \nWomen and People with disabilities are encouraged to apply.\n \n \n \n \n ",
                " \n \n \n \n \nPART-TIME LECTURER POSITIONS\nFaculty of Science: Department of Biomedical Sciences\nRef: 24/82\nThe Faculty of Science: Department of Biomedical Sciences requires the services of Part-Time Lecturers for day classes at the Pretoria (Arcadia) Campus. \n \nKey performance areas \n\u2022 Preparing and conducting theory lecturers. \n\u2022 Advanced presentation skills (online and Face to Face). \n\u2022 Proven ability in using teaching technology (including myTUTor). \n\u2022 Setting and marking of all assessments. \n\u2022 Participating in programme and subject meetings. \n\u2022 General administration such as capturing test and assignment marks, uploading documents on myTUTor. \n\u2022 Consultation and interaction with industry where necessary. \n\u2022 Student consultation. \n \nMinimum Requirements: \n\u2022 M-Tech or similar Master\u2019s Degree to any of the subject fields below.\u2019 \n\u2022 Study record with major subjects. \n\u2022 Three (3) years teaching and or research experience at a tertiary institution will be required and/or industry related experience. \n\u2022 Proficiency in Ms Office computer programs. \n\u2022 Full proficiency in English reading, writing, and communicating is a prerequisite. \n\u2022 Registration with the Health Professional Council of South Africa as a graduate in Clinical Technology Practitioner (where applicable) \n\u2022 Completion of TUT license to Teach programme will be compulsory. \n \nSend your CV with application for employment form, certified copies of qualifications & ID to: BoshoffCI@tut.ac.za\n \nEnquiries: Dr Carin Boshoff \nClosing Date: 25 June 2024\n \nNUMBER OF HOURS\n2 contact hours per academic week (Theory)\nCampus: Arcadia\nSubject: Immunology (IMM115P)\nSend your CV to: BoshoffCI@tut.ac\n \nNUMBER OF HOURS\n2 contact hours per academic week (Theory)\n2.5 contact hours per academic week (Practical)\nCampus: Arcadia\nSubject: Immunohaematology (IHM216P)\nSend your CV to: BoshoffCI@tut.ac\n \nNB: If we have not responded within a month from the closing date, you should regard your application as being unsuccessful. Correspondence will only be entered into with short-listed candidates. All applications with international qualifications are required to submit a SAQA evaluation certificate. Preference will be given to people from designated groups and the University reserves the right, in its sole discretion, not to make an appointment. It is the intention of the University to promote representativity in respect of race, gender and disability through the filling of these posts. \n \nCandidates are also required to complete the application form for employment and attach certified copies of ID & Qualifications. The application is available on the University\u2019s website, share point and the University\u2019s intranet.\n \nWomen and People with disabilities are encouraged to apply.\n \n \n \n \n ",
                " \n \n \n \n \n The Faculty of Management Sciences requires the services of Part-Time lecturers for day classes in the Department of Marketing, Supply Chain and Sport Management \n \nCritical Performance Areas \n\u2022 Preparing and conducting lectures and practicals. \n\u2022 Advanced presentation skills. \n\u2022 Proven ability in using teaching technology. \n\u2022 Setting and marking of all assessments. \n\u2022 Participating in departmental meetings and subject meetings. \n\u2022 General administration such as capturing test and assignment marks on ITS, and uploading documents on myTUTor. \n\u2022 Student consultation. \n \nMinimum Requirements \n\u2022 Masters degree is required in the field of Sport Management \n\u2022 Study record with major subjects in undergraduate and post graduate studies. \n\u2022 At least three years\u2019 teaching experience at a tertiary institution will be required and/or relevant industry-related experience. \n\u2022 Proficiency in MS Office and other computer programs. \n\u2022 Full proficiency in English is a prerequisite. \n\u2022 Completion of a TUT License to Teach programme will be compulsory. \n\n \n \n Department of Marketing, Supply Chain and Sport Management \nPretoria Campus \n(Ref 24/394 \n \nSend your CV to: RecruitmentMLS@tut.ac.za\nEnquiries: Dr EM Wannenburg Tel 012 382 4699 wannenburgem@tut.ac.za\n \nInclude: Certified copies of your academic record, qualifications, and ID document \nSuccessful applicants only receive a part-time salary according to the TUT Policy. No additional remuneration for travel, relocation, etc. \n \nClosing date: 21 June 2024 \n \nIf we have not responded within a month from the closing date, you should regard your application as unsuccessful. Correspondence will only be with short-listed candidates. The University reserves the right not to make an appointment. \n\n \nCAMPUS: PRETORIA \nNUMBER OF HOURS: 6 hpw \nYear Subject \nDay Class \nGROUPS: 1 Group \n \nCOURSE: Diploma Sport Management\nSFR105D\n\u2022 Sport, Fitness and Recreation Studies \n \n \nCAMPUS: PRETORIA \nNUMBER OF HOURS: 12 hpw \nYear Subject \nDay Class \nGROUPS: 2 Groups \n \nCOURSE: Diploma Sport Management \nCPE205D\n\u2022 Coaching and Physical Education Studies II\n \nWomen and People with disabilities are encouraged to apply.\n \n \n \n ",
                " \n \n \n \nINTERNAL /EXTERNAL POSITION\n \nHEAD COACH TUT FOOTBALL EMALAHLENI (MEN\u2019S FOOTBALL TEAM)\nDEPARTMENT: DIRECTORATE OF SPORT AND RECREATION\nREF 24/582\n \nThe Directorate of Sport & Recreation has a position for a Football Head Coach, eMalahleni campus. The position has been identified and intended for all internal and external candidates. \n \nCritical Performance Areas \n\u2022 To coach TUT eMalahleni Men\u2019s Football Team in SAFA Regional League and other related competitions. \n\u2022 Planning, organizing and executing practice sessions according to the needs and demands of the team; \n\u2022 Plan and organize trials for talent identification and recruitment of new players to the club; \n\u2022 Mentoring players and resolve team issues; \n\u2022 Provide reports on development of players, matches etc; \n \nMinimum Requirements \n\u2022 Matric. Post matric qualifications will be an added advantage; \n\u2022 Caf C license, Caf B license will be an added advantage; \n\u2022 Coaching experience at Club, District or Provincial level; \n\u2022 Coaching in USSA/Varsity Football/Competitions will be an added advantage \n\u2022 Proficiency in English \n\u2022 Computer Literacy \n\u2022 Basic First Aid qualification level 1 or 2; \n\u2022 Code 8 or 10 Driver\u2019s license; \n\u2022 No criminal record \n \nSend your CV to: Fakudeem@tut.ac.za\n \nEnquiries: Mr ME Fakude. T 012 382 0878 \n \nClosing Date 26 June 2024 \n \nINSTRUCTIONS: Applicants are required to submit together with the CVs, a standardized application form available from the university intranet as well as recently certified copies of qualifications and Identity Document. Failure to comply with this instruction will disqualify the candidate. Further note that candidates may be expected to make a presentation or undergo competency testing. \n \nIf we have not responded within a Month from the closing date, you should regard your application as unsuccessful. Correspondence will only be entered into with short-listed candidates. The University reserves the right not to make an appointment. Candidates may be subjected to appropriate psychometric testing and other selections instruments. Preference will be given to candidates from the designated groups.\n \nWomen and People with disabilities are encouraged to apply.\n \n \n \n \n ",
                " \n \n \n \n \nPART-TIME MARKERS x 6\nFACULTY OF HUMANITIES\nDEPARTMENT OF PUBLIC MANAGEMENT/LAW, SAFETY AND SECURITY MANAGEMENT/APPLIED LANGUAGES\nMBOMBELA CAMPUS\nRef: 24/103\nThe Faculty of Humanities at the Mbombela Campus seeks to appoint markers in the department of Public Management, Law, Safety and Security Management and Applied Languages for the 2024 academic year. \n \nKey performance area \nThe marker (s) in the Faculty of Humanities, is an individual responsible for marking examination scripts. The candidate must be able to: \n\u2022 Provide marking in different modules offered in Communicated and Languages Related Modules, Law and the Public Affairs Programme; and \n\u2022 Compile a comprehensive report after each and every marking project. \n \nMinimum Requirements\n \nAcademic qualifications: \n\u2022 Master\u2019s degree in Language Practice/African Languages/Linguistics or Masters in Public Management/Public Affairs/Public Administration or Masters of Laws or equivalent relevant qualification is required. \n \nExperience:\n\u2022 Knowledge in Communication Science, Public Affairs and Law \n\u2022 Ability to marks assessments manually and online \n \nRegistration with professional body (if applicable): \n\u2022 None \n \nKnowledge and Skills \n\u2022 Basic computer skills such as Microsoft, Excel, and Power Point \n\u2022 Full proficiency in English is a prerequisite. \n \nSuccessful applicants only receive a part-time salary according to TUT Policy. No additional remuneration for travel, relocation, etc.\n \nSend your CV to: MorenaLM@tut.ac.za\nEnquiries: Academic Manager: Dr. YLP Majola: 012 382 3706 \n \nClosing Date: 26 June 2024 \n \nNB: Please complete the downloadable application form from the vacancy webmail. \nNB. If we have not responded within eight weeks from the closing date, you should regard your application as unsuccessful. Correspondence will only be entered into with short \u2013 listed candidates.\n \nWomen and People with disabilities are encouraged to apply.\n \n \n \n ",
                " \n \n \n \n \nPART-TIME CARD OPERATORS X 22\nCAMPUS PROTECTION SERVICES\nPRETORIA, SOSHANGUVE AND GA-RANKUWA CAMPUSES REF: 24/654\nThe Campus Protection Services seeks to appoint x 22 part-time Card Operators at the Pretoria, Soshanguve and Ga-Rankuwa campuses. \n \nKey performance areas/Core functions: \n\u2022 ID/Access Card Production \n\u2022 Administration \n\u2022 Student/Personnel liaison \n \nMinimum requirements: \nAcademic qualifications: \n\u2022 National Senior Certificate \n \nExperience:\n\u2022 None, training will be provided \n \nRegistration with a professional body (if applicable): \n\u2022 N/A \n \n \nSend your CV to the following email address: \n\u2022 Ga-Rankuwa to Mr H Mosoma - MosamaHM@tut.ac.za  \n\u2022 Pretoria to Mr K Chauke - ChaukeK@tut.ac.za\n\u2022 Soshanguve to Ms N Mathonsi - SebeshoRC@tut.ac.za  \n \nClosing Date : 18 June 2024 \n \nEnquiries : Mr SM Mphai, Tel: (012 382-4419) \n \nIf we have not responded within a month of the closing date, you should regard your application as unsuccessful. Correspondence will be entered into only with short-listed candidates. The University reserves the right not to make an appointment. It is the intention of the university to promote representatively in respect of race, gender, and disability through the filling of these posts. Preferences will be given to candidates from the designated groups. \n \nCandidates are also required to complete the application form for employment. The application is available on the University\u2019s website, share point and the University\u2019s intranet.\n \nWomen and People with disabilities are encouraged to apply.\n \n \n \n \n ",
                " \n \n \n \nPART TIME LECTURER FOR BIOETHICS\nFACULTY OF SCIENCE\nDEPARTMENT OF BIOTECHNOLOGY AND FOOD TECHNOLOGY\nREF NO:24/130\nThe Department of Biotechnology and Food Technology in Faculty of Science has a part time lecturer for Bioethics the position is available at Arcadia Campus. 10 hours per week over 6 weeks (Semester 2) \n \nINSTRUCTIONS: Applicants are required to submit together with the CVs, a standardized application form available from the university intranet as well as recently certified copies of qualifications, identity document and motivation letter. Failure to comply with this instruction will disqualify the candidate. Please include certified qualification and ID copy not less than three months \n \n1. Critical Performance Areas: \n\u2022 Preparing and conducting Lecturers \n\u2022 Advanced presentation skills \n\u2022 Proven ability in using Teaching Technology \n\u2022 Preparation of study materials (power point presentation, animations, videos and study notes) \n\u2022 To provide assignments, guide-tutorials and mentorship if required. \n\u2022 General administration such as capturing test and assignments marks, uploading documents on myTUTOR \n\u2022 Setting and marking of all assessments (minimum of three (3) test covering work completed with the students over the course of the semester and three (3) exam papers in time for the departmental examination committee meeting and according to TUT guidelines) \n\u2022 To mark scripts (test and exams) and enter marks on the relevant platforms (including computing of marks on ITS system) before or on the departmental and Institutional due dates. \n\u2022 Be available for student consultation (at least three (3) hours during the block weeks \u2013 not including time in class) during a certain period \n \n2. Minimum Requirements: \n\u2022 Masters or Doctorate Degree relating to Bioethics \n \n3. Experience (minimum) \n\u2022 At least three (3) years relevant experience in teaching and/or research experience at a Tertiary Institution will be required and/or industry related experience \n\u2022 Full proficiency in English is a prerequisite \n \nSend your CV to: JordaanE@tut.ac.za, VisserMP@tut.ac.za and shongwenc@tut.ac.za\n \nEnquiries: Dr E Jordaan (Tel. 012 382 6214/6388) \n \nClosing date: 21 June 2024 \n \nNB. If we have not responded within a month from the closing date you should regard your application as unsuccessful. Correspondence will only be entered into with short-listed candidates. The University reserves the right not to make an appointment. It is the intention of the University to promote representatively in respect of race, gender and disability through the filling of these posts. Preference will be given to candidates from the designated groups.\n \nWomen and People with disabilities are encouraged to apply.\n \n \n \n \n ",
                " \n \n \n \n \nPART-TIME LECTURER X 1\nELECTRICAL ENGINEERING\nEMALAHLENI CAMPUS\nREF: 24/580\n \nThe Department of Electrical Engineering, Faculty of Engineering and the Built Environment has a part-time lecturer position in Automation at the eMalahleni Campus.\n \nCritical Performance Areas \n\u2022 Presenting lectures and tutorials for Automation (AUT216D) (Diploma Subject). \n\u2022 Setting of exam and assessment question papers and marking of scripts. \n\u2022 Keeping up-to-date subject files for each subject taught. \n\u2022 Preparing practical activities for each subject and supervising and evaluating individual project work. \n\u2022 Be responsible for all general admin work related to the subjects, including updating study guides and lecturer materials on MyTUTor and uploading assessment marks on ITS. \n\u2022 Quality teaching and learning with technology. \n\u2022 Implementing faculty\u2019s teaching and learning strategy with evidence. \n\u2022 Ensuring that all students do lecturer assessments on myTUTor. \n\u2022 Ensuring that all allocated subjects adhere to assessment structure and time frames (submission of marks, moderators, and other related processes) \n\u2022 Motivating and reminding students to register (activate) their TUT4Life free email account. \n\u2022 Using TUT4Life as the default means of communication for allocated subjects. \n\u2022 Making all announcements regarding my subject(s) in class and on myTUTor. If an announcement has not also been posted to my group(s) on myTUTor then an announcement is not formal. \n\u2022 Sending email reminders to all students at least three days before the deadline for projects, assignments and test dates. Take note that myTUTor can be configured to do this automatically. \n \nMinimum Requirements \nA minimum of MEng/ MTech/ MScEng qualifications in Electrical Engineering \n \nExperience\n\u2022 Must have at least three years of lecturing experience in an institution of higher learning or at least three years of industry experience in Electrical Engineering \n\u2022 Subject\u2019s Experience with Blackboard/myTUTor or other online content management systems will be advantageous. \n \nRegistration with a professional body (if applicable) \nSend your CV to: vanniekerkme@tut.ac.za\nEnquiries: Ms. Marlize van Niekerk \nPhone: +27 12 382-3130 \n \nClosing Date: 21 June 2024 \n \nIf we have yet to respond within a Month from the closing date, you should regard your application as unsuccessful. Correspondence will only be entered into with short-listed candidates. The University reserves the right not to make an appointment. Candidates must undergo psychometric testing and any other simulation intervention.\n \nWomen and People with disabilities are encouraged to apply.\n \n \n \n \n \n ",
                " \n \n \n \n \nPART TIME LECTURERS x 2\nPERIOD (01 JULY \u2013 31 DECEMBER 2024)\nFACULTY OF ECONOMIC AND FINANCE - POLOKWANE CAMPUS\nREF: 24/331\nThe Faculty of Economics and Finance requires the services of Part-time lecturers for day and evening classes at the Polokwane Campus. \nDay classes start from 08:00 \u2013 17:00 & Night Classes Start from 17:00 \u2013 22:00 \n \nCritical Performance Areas \n\u2022 Preparing and conducting lectures both distance and contact \n\u2022 Advanced presentation skills for both contact/distance mode \n\u2022 Proven ability in conducting teaching with technology. \n\u2022 Setting and marking of all assessments both contact/distance \n\u2022 Participating in departmental meetings and subject meetings \n\u2022 General administration such as capturing test and assignment marks, compiling of learning material, printing class lists, uploading documents such as teaching materials on the official LMS platform of the University. \n\u2022 Student consultation/communication for both contact/distance \n \nMinimum Requirements \n\u2022 Honours - CA(SA), or Master\u2019s degree relating to the field of study below. \n\u2022 Study record with major subjects listed. \n\u2022 At least three years teaching (contact and distance) and/or research experience at a tertiary institution will be required and/or industry related experience. \n\u2022 Excellent writing, oral, communication, presentation, and computer skills. \n\u2022 Proficiency in MS Office as well as other teaching and learning with technology software. \n\u2022 Full proficiency in English is a prerequisite. \n\u2022 Progress towards a masters\u2019 degree will be a strong recommendation. \n\u2022 Member of a professional body will be an added advantage. \n\u2022 Completion of a TUT License to Teach programme will be compulsory once appointed. \n \nExperience\n\u2022 Study record with major subjects listed. \n\u2022 At least three years teaching and distance end all research experience at each treasury institution will be required and all industry related experience. \n\u2022 Proficiency in MS. Office as well as other teaching and learning with technology software. \n\u2022 Full proficiency in English is a prerequisite. \n\u2022 Completion of a duty license to teach program will be compulsory once appointed. \n \nRegistration with professional body if applicable \n\u2022 Be a member of any professional bodies recognized by the faculty i.e. ACCA, CIMA, SAIPA, SAIGA, CIGFARO, ESSA other related bodies if advisable but not compulsive not compulsory. \n \nSubjects to be lectured as grouped together for Day classes and Night classes. \nAdvanced Diploma: Internal Auditing (Evening classes) - 1 \n\u2022 Audit Software Systems IVA (ASB117V); INTERNAL AUDIT IVA (IAB117V); WIL in Auditing (Simulation) IVA (WIB117V) \nDiploma: Internal Auditing (Day classes) \n\u2022 Public Sector Governance, Control II (RMO316D); \nDiploma: Public Sector Finance (Day classes) \n\u2022 Public Finance Law III (PFW316D); \nDiploma: Accounting (Day classes) \n\u2022 Professional Standards and Ethics I (PAG105D); \n \nDiploma: Financial Management (Day classes) \n\u2022 e-Business II (EBE216D) \n \nSend your CV to: recuitmentpol@tut.ac.za\n \nClosing Date: 21 June 2024 \n \nEnquiries : Mr MW Madia \u2013 012 382 0921 \n \nIf we have not responded within a month of the closing date, you should regard your application as unsuccessful. Correspondence will be entered into only with short-listed candidates. The University reserves the right not to make an appointment. It is the intention of the university to promote representatively in respect of race, gender, and disability through the filling of these posts. Preferences will be given to candidates from the designated groups. \n \nCandidates are also required to complete the application form for employment. The application is available on the University\u2019s website, share point and the University\u2019s intranet.\n \nWomen and People with disabilities are encouraged to apply.\n \n \n \n \n ",
                "PART-TIME LECTURERS\nDEPARTMENT OF INFORMATICS\nFACULTY OF ICT\nSOSHANGUVE SOUTH CAMPUS\nREF: 24/653\n \nThe Department of Informatics in the Faculty of ICT seeks to appoint Part-time Lecturers at the Soshanguve South campus to teach the following subjects: \nDiploma in Informatics \u2013 During the week (7 Posts) \nBCMF15D 2 Business Cost Management \nBFSF15D 3 Business Fundamentals \nBUB216D 1 Business Analysis B \nDBB216D 1 Database Management B \n \nAdvanced Diploma in Informatics \u2013 Saturdays (2 Post) \nIAR117V 1 Information Systems Architecture \nSIS117V 1 Strategic Information Systems \n \nKey performance areas/Core functions: \nPreparing all lecture materials, assessments, and memorandums for related subjects. \nPreparing lectures and assessing students registered for the subject. \nPerforming administration of marks and other related administrative duties under the Subject head, Section head, and HOD supervision. \nAttend staff and subject meetings, and \nAdhere to the due dates set by the Section head. \n \nMinimum requirements for Diploma (Main and Extended Qualification) \nAcademic qualifications and others: \nBTech: IT Business Applications; or \nBTech: IT Business Information Systems; or \nPostgraduate Diploma in Informatics. \n \nMinimum requirements for Advanced Diploma \nAcademic qualifications and others: \nMTech: IT Business Applications; or \nMTech: IT Business Information Systems; or \nMaster in Computing in Informatics \n \nExperience:\nAt least one (1) year of lecturing experience in a tertiary environment within the fields mentioned below; or \nAt least two (2) years of industry in the fields of business analysis, system analysis, IT project management, enterprise architecture, knowledge management, strategic and design science research.\n \nRegistration with a professional body (if applicable): \nN/A\n \nSend CVs to : VanRooyenM@tut.ac.za\nEnquiries : Dr RC Mogase (012 382-9310) \n \nClosing date: 18 June 2024 \n\nCandidates must be able to travel to campus during the week and on short notice and be available for face-to-face classes and/or assessment over the weekends (which could include long weekends). \nTCA: Please note that the department reserves the right not to employ for the advertised positions. \nCertified copies of academic qualifications must be attached to the application. \nThe application will not be considered if the applicant doesn\u2019t attach a CV and certified copies of the academic qualification. \n \nIf we have not responded within a month of the closing date, you should regard your application as unsuccessful. Correspondences will be entered into only with short-listed candidates. The University reserves the right not to make an appointment. It is the intention of the university to promote representatively in respect of race, gender and disability through the filling of these posts. Preferences will be given to candidates from the designated groups.\n \nCandidates are also required to complete the application form for employment. The application is available on the University\u2019s website, share point and the University\u2019s intranet.\n \nWomen and People with disabilities are encouraged to apply.",
                "PART TIME LECTURERS (2X) (2024):\nFACULTY OF ENGINEERING AND THE BUILT ENVIRONMENT\nDEPARTMENT OF ARCHITECTURE AND INDUSTRIAL DESIGN\nPRETORIA WEST CAMPUS\nREF: 24/ 607\n \nThe Department of Architecture and Industrial Design requires the services of part-time lecturers to teach the listed architecture subjects in the Master\u2019s degree, in the Faculty of Engineering and the Built Environment at the Pretoria Campus. All part-time lecturers are remunerated using the official TUT hourly tariffs. All part-time lecturing appointments are limited to a maximum of 19 hours per week: \n \nMArch Prof (MPAR18) \n \nFIRST YEAR \nARCHITECTURAL DESIGN V (ACH109M) \nOne (1) post available \nContact hours = 2 days/week x 4 contact hours/day x 15 weeks Total tuition time = 120 hours \n \nSECOND YEAR \nCONTRACT DOCUMENTATION V (CDO209M) \nOne (1) post available \nContact hours = 1 day/week x 3.5 contact hours/day x 15 weeks Total tuition time = 52.5 hours \n \nMinimum Requirements \n\u2022 Academic qualifications: Master\u2019s degree in Architecture, or HEQSF equivalent (5-year BArch degree). \n\u2022 Registration with the South African Council for the Architectural Profession (SACAP) will be advantageous. \n\u2022 Registration with a voluntary Architectural body such as the PIA / SAIA will be advantageous. \n \nCritical performance arrears: \n\u2022 Lecturing of the above-named subjects. \n\u2022 Standard academic duties and responsibilities. \n\u2022 Evaluate students on a continuous basis as well as administer tests and assignments according to study guides. \n\u2022 Community service and Industry Liaison. \n\u2022 Research, innovation or community involvement \n\u2022 Setting, preparing and conducting lectures for the subjects. \n\u2022 Marking assignments and tests and conducting practicals. \n\u2022 Participating in departmental meetings and subject meetings. \n\u2022 General administration such as capturing test and assignment marks on ITS System, uploading documents on myTUTor and compiling of subject file(s). \n\u2022 Student consultation. \n \nExperience\n\u2022 A minimum of three (3) years teaching experience in Architecture or in related CPD courses. \n\u2022 Experience of working in a high-quality academic research environment. \n\u2022 An ability to teach, mentor and guide students. \n\u2022 Experience of critical formative assessment of design and theory, as well as general experience offering construction at under-graduate levels. \n\u2022 Presentation of practical classes and critique of designs on group and individual basis. \n \nKnowledge and Skills: \n\u2022 Excellent communication and interpersonal skills which give you the ability to engage with students, colleagues, business and other agencies on a wide variety of matters. \n\u2022 Working as a member of a coordinated team. \n \nPlease send your CV to: labuschagnemm@tut.ac.za  \nEnquiries: Dr Tarien\u00e9 Gaum \nEmail: LabuschagneMM@tut.ac.za\nTel: 012 382 4214 / 5252 \n \nClosing Date: 17 June 2024 \n \nIf we have not responded within a month of the closing date, you should regard your application as unsuccessful. Correspondence will be entered into only with short-listed candidates. Candidates may be required to undergo psychometric tests and any other simulation interventions. People with disabilities are encouraged to apply. Preference will be given to people from designated groups and the University reserves the right, in its sole discretion, not to make an appointment. \n \nINSTRUCTIONS: Applicants are required to submit together with the CVs, academic records, a standardized application form available from the university intranet as well as recently certified copies of qualifications and Identity Document. Failure to comply with this instruction will disqualify the candidate. Further note that candidates may be expected to make a presentation or undergo competency testing.\n \nWomen and People with disabilities are encouraged to apply."
