                " \nEKURHULENI WEST TVET COLLEGE\n ",
                " \n \n \nVACANCY: POST LEVEL 1 LECTURER (PERMANENT) - BUSINESS STUDIES - KATHORUS CAMPUS\n \nEKURHULENI WEST TVET COLLEGE INVITES QUALIFIED AND EXPERIENCED CANDIDATES TO APPLY FOR THE FOLLOWING VACANCY TO BE FILLED ACCORDING TO THE CET ACT NO. 16 OF 2006 AS AMENDED.\n \nPost Designation:\nPost Level 1 Lecturer (Permanent)\nReference Number:\nEWC/KAT/08/2024.\n \nMinimum Salary:\nR256 395 \u2013 R410 565 per annum, plus benefits.\n \nEducational Requirements:\nA National Senior Certificate (Matric);\nNational Diploma/Degree in Business Studies;\nTVET Education Lecturing Qualification.\n \nMinimum Requirements:\nA minimum of zero to two (0-2) years\u2019 experience in the TVET Sector;\nRegistered with South African Council for Educators (SACE);\nModerator and Assessor certificate will be an added advantage;\nDriver's licence will be an added advantage.\n \nPost Description:\nLife Skills and Computer Literacy Level 2-4.\n \nDuties:\nEngage in learning / facilitating as per workload;\nAssess and record the performance of students;\nProvide guidance on the latest developments on approaches to the program.\n \nClosing Date For Applications:\n20 June 2024 (Thursday);\nApplications received after the closing date will not be accepted.\n \nEnquiries:\nKindly contact the Human Resource Department - Ms MN Phakathi 010 023 3762.\n \nCandidates Are Required To Submit The Following Documents:\nA NEW Z83: Application for Employment Form, effective from 01 January 2021 (those who use the old Z83 will be disqualified), obtainable from any Public Service Department, or here: Z83: Application for Employment Form;\nA comprehensive CV with three (3) contactable references, with email addresses;\nOriginal certified copy of SACE Certificate;\nOriginal certified copies of qualifications (evaluated by DHET and SAQA, if foreign);\nOriginal certified copies of academic record/transcript;\nOriginal certified copy of driver's licence (front and back);\nOriginal certified copy of identity document (back and front, if a card).\n \nShortlisted candidates will go through a vetting process (citizenship, criminal check, verification of qualifications, social media, and credit check).\n \nApplications should be posted or hand delivered to Ekurhuleni West TVET College (Kathorus Campus), Cnr Poole & Thutong Streets, Katlehong 1457.\n \nPlease mark the application with the post title and reference number. Closing date: 20 June 2024.\n \n Correspondence will be entered into with short-listed candidates and the successful applicants. Applicants should kindly note that if the notice of appointment has not been received within 30 days of the closing date, it must be assumed that the application has been unsuccessful.\n \nAfrican, White and Coloured males, and people with disabilities are highly encouraged to apply for this position in line with the Ekurhuleni West TVET College Employment Equity targets.\n \nEKURHULENI WEST COLLEGE IS AN EQUAL OPPORTUNITIES EMPLOYER. THE COLLEGE RESERVES THE RIGHT TO NOT FILL THE POST.\n \n \n \n \n ",
                " \n \n \n \n \n \nVACANCY: POST LEVEL 1 LECTURER (PERMANENT) - BUSINESS STUDIES - KATHORUS CAMPUS\n\n \nEKURHULENI WEST TVET COLLEGE INVITES QUALIFIED AND EXPERIENCED CANDIDATES TO APPLY FOR THE FOLLOWING VACANCY TO BE FILLED ACCORDING TO THE CET ACT NO. 16 OF 2006 AS AMENDED.\n \nPost Designation:\nPost Level 1 Lecturer (Permanent)\nReference Number:\nEWC/KAT/08/2024.\n \nMinimum Salary:\nR256 395 \u2013 R410 565 per annum, plus benefits.\n \nEducational Requirements:\nA National Senior Certificate (Matric);\nNational Diploma/Degree in Business Studies;\nTVET Education Lecturing Qualification.\n \nMinimum Requirements:\nA minimum of zero to two (0-2) years\u2019 experience in the TVET Sector;\nRegistered with South African Council for Educators (SACE);\nModerator and Assessor certificate will be an added advantage;\nDriver's licence will be an added advantage.\n \nPost Description:\nLife Skills and Computer Literacy Level 2-4.\n \nDuties:\nEngage in learning / facilitating as per workload;\nAssess and record the performance of students;\nProvide guidance on the latest developments on approaches to the program.\n \nClosing Date For Applications:\n20 June 2024 (Thursday);\nApplications received after the closing date will not be accepted.\n \nEnquiries:\nKindly contact the Human Resource Department - Ms MN Phakathi 010 023 3762.\n \nCandidates Are Required To Submit The Following Documents:\nA NEW Z83: Application for Employment Form, effective from 01 January 2021 (those who use the old Z83 will be disqualified), obtainable from any Public Service Department, or here: Z83: Application for Employment Form;\nA comprehensive CV with three (3) contactable references, with email addresses;\nOriginal certified copy of SACE Certificate;\nOriginal certified copies of qualifications (evaluated by DHET and SAQA, if foreign);\nOriginal certified copies of academic record/transcript;\nOriginal certified copy of driver's licence (front and back);\nOriginal certified copy of identity document (back and front, if a card).\n \nShortlisted candidates will go through a vetting process (citizenship, criminal check, verification of qualifications, social media, and credit check).\n \nApplications should be posted or hand delivered to Ekurhuleni West TVET College (Kathorus Campus), Cnr Poole & Thutong Streets, Katlehong 1457.\n \nPlease mark the application with the post title and reference number. Closing date: 20 June 2024.\n \n Correspondence will be entered into with short-listed candidates and the successful applicants. Applicants should kindly note that if the notice of appointment has not been received within 30 days of the closing date, it must be assumed that the application has been unsuccessful.\n \nAfrican, White and Coloured males, and people with disabilities are highly encouraged to apply for this position in line with the Ekurhuleni West TVET College Employment Equity targets.\n \nEKURHULENI WEST COLLEGE IS AN EQUAL OPPORTUNITIES EMPLOYER. THE COLLEGE RESERVES THE RIGHT TO NOT FILL THE POST.\n \n \n \n \n ",
                " \n \n \n \n \nVACANCY: POST LEVEL 1 LECTURER (PERMANENT) - GERMISTON CAMPUS\n \nEKURHULENI WEST TVET COLLEGE INVITES QUALIFIED AND EXPERIENCED CANDIDATES TO APPLY FOR THE FOLLOWING VACANCY TO BE FILLED ACCORDING TO THE CET ACT NO. 16 OF 2006 AS AMENDED.\n \nPost Designation:\nPost Level 1 Lecturer (Permanent)\nReference Number:\nEWC/GERM/04/2024.\n \nMinimum Salary:\nR256 395 \u2013 R410 565 per annum, plus benefits.\n \nEducational Requirements:\nA National Senior Certificate (Matric);\nNational Diploma/Degree in Mathematics;\nTVET Education Lecturing Qualification.\n \nMinimum Requirements:\nA minimum of zero to one (0-1) years\u2019 experience in the TVET Sector;\nRegistered with South African Council for Educators (SACE);\nModerator and Assessor certificate will be an added advantage;\nDriver's licence will be an added advantage;\n \nPost Description:\nPure Mathematics N4-N6.\n \nDuties:\nEngage in learning / facilitating as per workload;\nAssess and record the performance of students;\nManage a learning program;\nDevelop the policy for the program;\nProvide guidance on the latest developments on approaches to the program;\n \nClosing Date For Applications:\n23 June 2024 (Sunday);\nApplications received after the closing date will not be accepted.\n \nEnquiries:\nKindly contact the Human Resource Department - Ms T Peter 011) 876-6900.\n \nCandidates Are Required To Submit The Following Documents:\nA NEW Z83: Application for Employment Form, effective from 01 January 2021 (those who use the old Z83 will be disqualified), obtainable from any Public Service Department, or here: Z83: Application for Employment Form;\nA comprehensive CV with three (3) contactable references, with email addresses;\nOriginal certified copy of SACE Certificate;\nOriginal certified copies of qualifications (evaluated by DHET and SAQA, if foreign);\nOriginal certified copies of academic record/transcript;\nOriginal certified copy of driver's licence (front and back, if it is a card);\nOriginal certified copy of identity document (back and front, if a card).\n \nShortlisted candidates will go through a vetting process (citizenship, criminal check, verification of qualifications, social media, and credit check).\n \nApplications should be posted or hand delivered to Ekurhuleni West TVET College (Germiston Campus), Cnr Driehoek and Sol Roads, Germiston 1400.\n \nPlease mark the application with the post title and reference number.\n \nMales across all races, white females and people with disabilities are highly encouraged to apply for this position in line with the Ekurhuleni West TVET College Employment Equity targets.\n \nCorrespondence will be entered into with short-listed candidates and the successful applicants. Applicants should kindly note that if the notice of appointment has NOT been received within 30 days of the closing date, it must be assumed that the application has been unsuccessful.\n \nEKURHULENI WEST COLLEGE IS AN EQUAL OPPORTUNITIES EMPLOYER. THE COLLEGE RESERVES THE RIGHT NOT TO FILL THE POST.\n \n \n \n \n ",
                "VACANCY: PL1 LECTURER (PERMANENT) - GERMISTON CAMPUS\n \nEKURHULENI WEST TVET COLLEGE INVITES QUALIFIED AND EXPERIENCED CANDIDATES TO APPLY FOR THE FOLLOWING VACANCY TO BE FILLED ACCORDING TO THE CET ACT NO. 16 OF 2006 AS AMENDED.\n \nPost Designation:\nPost Level 1 Lecturer (Permanent)\nReference Number:\nEWC/GERM/05/2024.\n \nMinimum Salary:\nR256 395 \u2013 R410 565 per annum, plus benefits.\n \nEducational Requirements:\nA National Senior Certificate (Matric);\nNational Diploma/Degree in Electrical Engineering;\nTVET Education Lecturing Qualification.\n \nMinimum Requirements:\nA minimum of zero to one (0-1) years\u2019 experience in the TVET Sector;\nRegistered with South African Council for Educators (SACE);\nModerator and Assessor certificate will be an added advantage;\nDriver's licence is an added advantage.\n \nPost Description:\nIndustrial Electronics N4-N6;\nElectro Technics N4-N6.\n \nDuties:\nEngage in learning / facilitating as per workload;\nAssess and record the performance of students;\nManage a learning program;\nDevelop the policy for the program;\nProvide guidance on the latest developments on approaches to the program;\n \nClosing Date For Applications:\n23 June 2024 (Sunday);\nApplications received after the closing date will not be accepted.\n \nEnquiries:\nKindly contact the Human Resource Department - Ms T Peter 011 876 6900.\n \nCandidates Are Required To Submit The Following Documents:\nA NEW Z83: Application for Employment Form, effective from 01 January 2021 (those who use the old Z83 will be disqualified), obtainable from any Public Service Department, or here: Z83: Application for Employment Form;\nA comprehensive CV with three (3) contactable references, with email addresses;\nOriginal certified copy of SACE Certificate;\nOriginal certified copies of qualifications (evaluated by DHET and SAQA, if foreign);\nOriginal certified copies of academic record/transcript;\nOriginal certified copy of driver's licence (front and back);\nOriginal certified copy of identity document (back and front, if a card).\n \nShortlisted candidates will go through a vetting process (citizenship, criminal check, verification of qualifications, social media, and credit check).\n \nApplications should be posted or hand delivered to Ekurhuleni West TVET College (Germiston Campus), Cnr Driehoek & Sol Roads, Germiston 1400.\n \nPlease mark the application with the post title and reference number.\n \nMales across all races, white females and people with disabilities are highly encouraged to apply for this position in line with the Ekurhuleni West TVET College Employment Equity targets.\n \nCorrespondence will be entered into with short-listed candidates and the successful applicants. Applicants should kindly note that if no notice of appointment has been received within 30 days of the closing date, it must be assumed that the application has been unsuccessful.\n \nEKURHULENI WEST COLLEGE IS AN EQUAL OPPORTUNITIES EMPLOYER. THE COLLEGE RESERVES THE RIGHT NOT TO FILL THE POST.",
                "VACANCY: POST LEVEL 1 LECTURER (TEMPORARY) - TEMBISA CAMPUS\n \nEKURHULENI WEST TVET COLLEGE INVITES QUALIFIED AND EXPERIENCED CANDIDATES TO APPLY FOR THE FOLLOWING VACANCY TO BE FILLED ACCORDING TO THE CET ACT NO. 16 OF 2006 AS AMENDED.\n \nPost Designation:\nPost Level 1 Lecturer (Temporary)\nReference Number:\nEWC/TEM/03/2024.\n \nMinimum Salary:\nR256 395 \u2013 R410 565 per Annum, plus 37% in lieu of benefits.\n \nEducational Requirements:\nA National Senior Certificate (Matric);\nNational Diploma/Degree;\nTVET Education Lecturing Qualification.\n \nMinimum Requirements:\nA minimum of zero to two (0-2) years\u2019 experience in the TVET Sector;\nRegistered with South African Council for Educators (SACE);\nModerator and Assessor certificate will be an added advantage;\nDriver's licence will be an added advantage.\n \nPost Description:\nLife Skills and Computer Literacy L2-L4.\n \nDuties:\nEngage in learning / facilitating as per workload;\nAssess and record the performance of students;\nManage a learning program;\nDevelop the policy for the program;\nProvide guidance on the latest developments on approaches to the program;\n \nClosing Date For Applications:\n21 June 2024 (Friday, at 13h00);\nApplications received after the closing date will not be accepted.\n \nEnquiries:\nKindly contact the Human Resource Department - Ms RS Makopo: 010 023 3763.\n \nCandidates Are Required To Submit The Following Documents:\nA NEW Z83: Application for Employment Form, effective from 01 January 2021 (those who use the old Z83 will be disqualified), obtainable from any Public Service Department, or here: Z83: Application for Employment Form;\nA comprehensive CV with three (3) contactable references, with email addresses;\nOriginal certified copy of SACE Certificate;\nOriginal certified copies of qualifications (evaluated by DHET and SAQA, if foreign);\nOriginal certified copies of academic record/transcript;\nOriginal certified copy of identity document (back and front, if a card);\nOriginal certified copy of driver's licence (back and front).\n \nShortlisted candidates will go through a vetting process (citizenship, criminal check, verification of qualifications, social media, and credit check).\n \nApplications should be posted or hand delivered to Ekurhuleni West TVET College (Tembisa Campus), 09 Morogoro Street, Esiqongweni Section, Tembisa.\n \nPlease mark the application with the post title and reference number.\n \nCorrespondence will be entered into with short-listed candidates and the successful applicants. Applicants should kindly note that if the notice of appointment has not been received within 30 days of the closing date, it must be assumed that the application has been unsuccessful.\n \nMales across all races, white females, and people with disabilities are highly encouraged to apply for this position in line with the Ekurhuleni West TVET College Employment Equity targets.\n \nEKURHULENI WEST COLLEGE IS AN EQUAL OPPORTUNITIES EMPLOYER. THE COLLEGE RESERVES THE RIGHT NOT TO FILL THE POST."
